<h1>Time for Activity</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @Vru{{}} @KJ{{time^interval}}
<li> @Vru{{}} @KJ{{promise^bundle}}
<li> @Vru{{}} @KJ{{utilize^matter}}
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
When expressing the time at which some activity should be performed, place the dictionary form of the verb before @HI{{jikann}}.
To express the content of an appointment or other arrangement, place the dictionary form of the verb before @HI{{yakusoku}}
or @HI{{youji}} etc.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ha @KJ{{morning}}gohanwo @KJ{{eat}}beru@KJ{{time^interval}}ga arimasenn.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I have no time to eat breakfast.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ha @KJ{{friend^accomplished}}to @KJ{{reflect^brush-stroke}}wo @KJ{{see}}ru @KJ{{promise^bundle}} ga arimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I have an arrangement to see a film with a friend of mine.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kyouha @KJ{{market^duty^place}}he @KJ{{going}}ku @KJ{{utilize^matter}}ga arimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I have something to do at the town hall today.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

